7. FREE USE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following Uses are free of any payment obligation:

7.1 PERSONAL USE
    Personal Use for research, experiment, testing for the benefit of public
    knowledge, personal study, private entertainment, hobby projects, amateur
    pursuits, or religious observance, without any anticipated commercial
    application.

7.2 NONCOMMERCIAL ORGANIZATIONS
    Use by any charitable organization, educational institution, public
    research organization, public safety or health organization, environmental
    protection organization, or government institution, regardless of the
    source of funding or obligations arising from the funding.

7.3 CONTRIBUTIONS BACK
    Developing feedback, changes, or additions that You contribute back to
    Licensor under the terms of a standardized public software license such as
    the Blue Oak Model License 1.0.0, the Apache License 2.0, the MIT license,
    or the two-clause BSD license.

7.4 SMALL BUSINESS USE
    Commercial Use during any Fiscal Year in which the aggregate Gross Revenue
    of You and all Your Affiliates was less than One Million United States
    Dollars ($1,000,000 USD) in the most recently completed Fiscal Year.

7.5 EVALUATION
    Commercial evaluation and trial Use for a single period of up to ninety
    (90) consecutive days to determine suitability for Your needs. The
    evaluation period is available once per entity (including Affiliates);
    continued Commercial Use after it ends is subject to Section 8.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8. COMMERCIAL USE — REVENUE SHARING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

For Commercial Use not covered by Section 7:

8.1 CONTRIBUTION
    For each Fiscal Year of Commercial Use, You must contribute EITHER:
    (a) three percent (3%) of Attributable Revenue for that Fiscal Year; OR
    (b) one half of one percent (0.5%) of Gross Revenue for that Fiscal Year.
    You elect (a) or (b) in Your first compliance report for that Fiscal Year;
    the election is binding for that Fiscal Year once made.

8.2 SCHEDULE
    Contributions are due within ninety (90) days after the end of each Fiscal
    Year. The first contribution is due after the first Fiscal Year (or part
    thereof) of Commercial Use following any evaluation period.

8.3 REPORTING
    With each contribution, submit a compliance report to licensing@gestura.ai
    stating: the Fiscal Year covered; the election made under 8.1; the revenue
    figures and calculation methodology used; and contact information for
    verification. Reports are Confidential Information of You; Licensor will
    use them only for license administration and will not disclose them except
    as required by law.

8.4 PAYMENT MECHANISMS
    - Direct payment to Gestura AI LLC (instructions from licensing@gestura.ai)
    - GitHub Sponsors: https://github.com/sponsors/gestura-ai
    - Open Collective: https://opencollective.com/gestura

